Hello <%= @email %>,

Re: <%= @subject %>

WELCOME TO POSTCARDMAILER.US!

Thank you for requesting help with PostcardMailer.us. Below you'll find instructions for using our service through email commands.

AVAILABLE COMMANDS:

1. SIGN UP
   To create a new account:
   - Send an email to signup@postcardmailer.us
   - Include your full name in the subject line
   - In the email body, include your complete mailing address

   Example:
   To: signup@postcardmailer.us
   Subject: John Smith
   Body: 123 Main Street
         San Francisco, CA 94110

2. ADD AN ADDRESS
   To add a new address to your account:
   - Send an email to adduser@postcardmailer.us
   - Include a nickname for this address in the subject line
   - In the email body, include the recipient's name and address

   Example:
   To: adduser@postcardmailer.us
   Subject: mom
   Body: Jane Smith
         456 Oak Avenue
         Chicago, IL 60601

   Note: Our AI-powered address parser will automatically standardize and validate 
   the address format to ensure accurate delivery through the US Postal Service.

3. SEND A POSTCARD
   To send a postcard to someone in your address book:
   - Send an email to $nickname@postcardmailer.us
   - Use the subject line for the message to the recipient
   - Attach the image you want to use for the postcard

   Example:
   To: mom@postcardmailer.us
   Subject: Had a great time in San Francisco!
   Attachment: vacation-photo.jpg

4. GET HELP
   To receive these instructions again:
   - Send an email to help@postcardmailer.us

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- New accounts require verification before you can send postcards
- Make sure addresses are complete and formatted correctly
- Image attachments should be clear and high resolution for best results
- The subject line is used to identify the recipient by their nickname

If you have any other questions or need assistance, please reply to this email.

